The paper deals with the problem of drawing binary tanglegrams, which involves rooted binary trees and their leaf sets. This suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem is also related to graph theory and optimization, which could place it in the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), or game theory (cs.GT).
